Usage: encrypt [-help] <input_file_name> [-pragma] [> <file>] [-tcl  | -verilog ]

-help                 # Prints out the command usage
<input_file_name>     # Specifies the file to be encrypted. (string, required)
-pragma               # Specifies to only encrypt the text between the protect
                      # begin and protect end NC Protect pragmas. Encryption
                      # block must start with pragma protect comment.
                      # (bool, optional)
-tcl                  # Specifies that the file to be encrypted is a Tcl file.
                      # This is the default option. (bool, optional)
-verilog              # Uses Verilog style comments for NC Protect pragmas.
                      # (bool, optional)
> <file>              # Specifies the name of the encrypted file. By default,
                      # the encrypted file is printed to standard out (stdout).
                      # (redirect_operator, optional)